LINE.Text: In 1967 Israel occupied and illegally annexed Palestinian East Jerusalem in a move the UN Security Council said has "no legal
validity". Ever since, Israel has attempted to reduce the city's population of Palestinians and expand the illegal Jewish-Israell
settler population - The steps taken to achieve this goal include the isolation of East Jerusalem from the West Bank, land
theft, and discriminatory policies in planning, construction and budgeting. Although the annexation of East Jerusalem and its
residents was a decision made solely by Israel, Israeli authorities treat East Jerusalem Palestinians as if they had made a
voluntary decision to immigrate to Israel. Therefore, the authorities void Palestinians' residency status and social benefits if
they do not meet the restrictive criteria originally formulated for foreign residents.
